Reports when a `@Language` annotation is applied to an element with a type other than `String` or `String[]`.

**Example:**


      @Language("HTML") int i;

After the quick-fix is applied:


      int i;

fullDescription.text:
Reports when a method without any '@Pattern' annotation overrides a '@Pattern' annotated method. This does not prevent error-highlighting inside the editor, however the overriding method will not be checked at runtime. A quick fix is provided to add a '@Pattern' annotation that matches the one from the superclass method. This ensures the runtime-check instrumentation works correctly. Example: 'abstract class Parent {
    abstract @Pattern("\\d\\d-\\d\\d\\d") String getId();
  }
  class Child extends Parent {
    @Override String getId() { // warning here
      return "12-345";
    }
  }'

fullDescription.markdown:
Reports when a method without any `@Pattern` annotation overrides a `@Pattern` annotated method. This does not prevent error-highlighting inside the editor, however the overriding method will not be checked at runtime.


A quick fix is provided to add a `@Pattern` annotation that matches the one from the superclass method. This ensures the
runtime-check instrumentation works correctly.

**Example:**


      abstract class Parent {
        abstract @Pattern("\\d\\d-\\d\\d\\d") String getId();
      }
      class Child extends Parent {
        @Override String getId() { // warning here
          return "12-345";
        }
      }

Reports when a `@Pattern` annotation is applied to an element with a type other than `String`.

**Example:**


      @Pattern("\\d\\d") int i;

Reports when the ID of the language used in a `@Language` annotation is unknown.

**Example:**


      @Language("HMTL") String html;

