Reports concatenation with string literals that consist of one character.

These literals may be replaced with equivalent character literals, gaining some performance enhancement.

**Example:**


      String hello = hell + "o";

After the quick-fix is applied:


      String hello = hell + 'o';

fullDescription.text:
Reports unnecessary 'this' qualifier. Using 'this' to disambiguate a code reference is discouraged by many coding styles and may easily become unnecessary via automatic refactorings. Example: 'class Foo {
    int x;
    void foo() {
      this.x = 2;
    }
  }' After the quick-fix is applied: 'class Foo {
    int x;
    void foo() {
      x = 2;
    }
  }' Use the inspection settings to ignore assignments to fields. For instance, 'this.x = 2;' won't be reported, but 'int y = this.x;' will be.

fullDescription.markdown:
