Reports type parameters declared to extend a 'final' class. Suggests replacing the type parameter with the type of the specified 'final' class since 'final' classes cannot be extended. Example: 'void foo() {
    List<? extends Integer> list; // Warning: the Integer class is a final class
  }' After the quick-fix is applied: 'void foo() {
    List<Integer> list;
  }' This inspection depends on the Java feature 'Generics', which is available since Java 5.

