Reports non-static inner classes that implement 'java.io.Serializable', but do not define a 'serialVersionUID' field. Without a 'serialVersionUID' field, any change to the class will make previously serialized versions unreadable. It is strongly recommended that 'Serializable' non-static inner classes have a 'serialVersionUID' field, otherwise the default serialization algorithm may result in serialized versions being incompatible between compilers due to differences in synthetic accessor methods. A quick-fix is suggested to add the missing 'serialVersionUID' field. Example: 'class Outer {
      class Inner implements Serializable {}
