Reports 'equals()' calls that compare two arrays. Calling 'equals()' on an array compares identity and is equivalent to using '=='. Use 'Arrays.equals()' to compare the contents of two arrays, or 'Arrays.deepEquals()' for multi-dimensional arrays. Example: 'void sample(int[] first, int[] second){
    if (first.equals(second)) return;
