Reports calls to 'start()' on 'java.lang.Thread' or any of its subclasses during object construction. While occasionally useful, such constructs should be avoided due to inheritance issues. Subclasses of a class that launches a thread during the object construction will not have finished any initialization logic of their own before the thread has launched. This inspection does not report if the class that starts a thread is declared 'final'. Example: 'class MyThread extends Thread {
    MyThread() {
      start();
    }
  }'

