fullDescription.text:
Reports 'String' concatenations that can be simplified by replacing them with a string template. Example: 'String name = "Bob";
  String greeting = "Hello, " + name + ". You are " + 29 + " years old.";' After the quick-fix is applied: 'String name = "Bob";
  String greeting = STR."Hello, \{name}. You are 29 years old.";' This inspection depends on the Java feature 'String templates', which is available since Java 21-preview. New in 2023.3

