Reports classes that are declared 'final'. Final classes that extend a 'sealed' class or interface are not reported. Such classes can't be inherited and may indicate a lack of object-oriented design. Some coding standards discourage 'final' classes. Example: 'public final class Main {
  }' After the quick-fix is applied: 'public class Main {
