Reports loops with an 'if' statement that can end with 'break' without changing the semantics. This prevents redundant loop iterations. Example: 'boolean found = false;
  for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
    if (Objects.equals(value, arr[i])) {
      found = true;
    }
  }' After the quick-fix is applied: 'boolean found = false;
  for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
    if (Objects.equals(value, arr[i])) {
      found = true;
      break;
    }
  }' New in 2019.2

fullDescription.markdown:
Reports loops with an `if` statement that can end with `break` without changing the semantics. This prevents redundant loop iterations.

**Example:**


      boolean found = false;
      for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
        if (Objects.equals(value, arr[i])) {
          found = true;
        }
      }

After the quick-fix is applied:


      boolean found = false;
      for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
        if (Objects.equals(value, arr[i])) {
          found = true;
          break;
        }
      }

New in 2019.2

