fullDescription.text:
Reports 'public' constructors of 'abstract' classes. Constructors of 'abstract' classes can only be called from the constructors of their subclasses, declaring them 'public' may be confusing. The quick-fix makes such constructors protected. Example: 'public abstract class Foo {
    public Foo () { // warning: has 'public' modifier
        /* ... */
    }
  }' After the quick-fix is applied: 'public abstract class Foo {
    protected Foo () {
        /* ... */
    }
  }' Configure the inspection: Use the Ignore for non-public classes option below to ignore 'public' constructors in non-public classes.

