Reports references to inner classes that are not qualified with the name of the enclosing class. Example: 'import foo.Foo.Bar;

  class Foo {
    class Bar {}
  }

  class Baz {
    void f(Bar bar) {}
  }' After the quick-fix is applied: 'class Foo {
    class Bar {}
  }

  class Baz {
    void f(Foo.Bar bar) {}
  }' Use the inspection settings to ignore references to inner classes within the same class, which therefore do not require an import.

