fullDescription.text:
Reports conditions and expressions that are always true, false or null. Example (MySQL): 'CREATE TABLE t1 (a TEXT, b INT, c BOOLEAN);
SELECT a FROM t1 WHERE 'Cat' = 'Cat';
SELECT a FROM t1 WHERE 'Cat' = null;' The ''Cat' = 'Cat'' is always true and will be reported. The ''Cat' = null' is always null and will be reported.

